nt|The third scenario is "We have a spade trick", either the A@s or the K@s in partner's hand. In that scenario if we play a club now for partner to ruff he will be unable to play spades from his side. So he will exit with diamonds and then declarer playing A@h and another heart will make the hand since clubs provide discards for the spade loser.|
