nt|Sometimes our bridge senses will fool us. But if you count, the count is always right. 
Things as "he wouldn't have played in this way if..." or "I thought you had ..." or "Don't you asked for a ..." may be wrong but the count of the hand can't be wrong.
So whenever you think you have to do something try to count before. You will discover your assumptions are not right many times.|
